  <article id="concessions">

  <h1><a href="#" name="concessions"></a>Concessions</h1>

  <ul class="sources">
    <li id="cameroon_logging" class="flag cm">
    <strong>Cameroon - Logging</strong> <a href="http://wri-01.cartodb.com/tables/gfw2_cam_conc.shp">Download</a>
    <p>Logging within Cameroon’s forest estate occurs within designated areas called Forest Management Units (FMUs).  There are 114 FMUs in Cameroon which are further divided into logging concessions called annual allowable cuts (AACs), where selective logging is permitted.  There are 2988 concessions within Cameroon’s FMU system.  These logging permits require owners and operators to maintain permanent forest cover.  This data can be downloaded from World Resources Institute.</p>
    </li>
    <li id="central_african_republic_logging" class="flag cf">
    <strong>Central African Republic - Logging</strong> <a href="http://wri-01.cartodb.com/tables/caf_lc_1.shp">Download</a>
    <p>Forest concession data from Central African Republic represent areas permitted for selective logging.  There are 14 separate logging concessions currently in Central African Republic.</p>
    </li>
    <li id="democratic_republic_of_congo_logging" class="flag cd">
    <strong>Democratic Republic of Congo - Logging</strong> <a href="http://wri-01.cartodb.com/tables/gfw2_drc_conc.shp">Download</a>
    <p>Forest concession data for the Democratic Republic of Congo represent areas permitted for selective logging.  There are 80 active logging concessions in DRC. This data can be downloaded from World Resources Institute.</p>
    </li>
    <li id="democratic_republic_of_congo_mining" class="flag cd">
    <strong>Democratic Republic of Congo - Mining</strong> <a href="">???</a>
    <p>Description</p>
    </li>
    <li id="republic_of_congo_logging" class="flag cd">
    <strong>Republic of Congo - Logging</strong> <a href="http://wri-01.cartodb.com/tables/cog_lc_1.shp">Download</a>
    <p>Forest concession data for the Republic of Congo represent areas permitted for selective logging.  There are currently 63 separate logging concessions in Congo Brazzaville. This data can be downloaded from World Resources Institute.</p>
    </li>
    <li id="gabon_logging" class="flag ga">
    <strong>Gabon - Logging</strong> <a href="http://wri-01.cartodb.com/tables/gfw2_gab_conc.shp">Download</a>
    <p>Forest concession data from Gabon represent areas permitted for selective logging.  There are 627 separate logging concessions currently in Gabon. This data can be downloaded from World Resources Institute.  </p>
    </li>
    <li id="indonesia_oil" class="flag id">
    <strong>Indonesia - Oil palm</strong> <a href="http://appgis.dephut.go.id/appgis/" target="_blank">Visit</a>
    <p>Oil palm concession data represent current or planned oil palm plantation boundaries in Indonesia.  This dataset is provided by the Indonesia Ministry of Forestry.  This data is available for download from Ministry of Forestry website.</p>
